Frankly, I worked there. It was one of the worst places I have ever worked. The manager, Mark, changes the employees schedules around at the flip of a whim (with no reason to change it), he also consistently griped about the other employees to me (but would never do anything about his gripes about them), the other employees were not happy with how Mark was doing his job. Mark would also put me on closing, but never teach me to count the inventory or the register, Mark consistently calls patrons sweetie, darling, sugar, among other names of the same meaning which is truly unprofessional and inappropriate for any work environment. The back of the store where dishes are done and food is stored is so disorganized that it's always an adventure to find the product we need to put on the line.  Not to mention the fact that they don't serve soup like some Subway restaurants do, when I worked there there were no deals period, when the sliders came out they never decided on a specific special for them so they charged $1.99 for 1 slider (which is the size of 2 McDonald's chicken nuggets side by side. Mark was a very unpleasant manager. Mark always changed his shirts in the back instead of going to the restroom to change like a normal person would do.  All the employees had problems with the way things ran there and have discussed them with Mark, who did nothing to fix the problem. The prep for Monday is always done on Saturday and Mark would have us pre-date the food prepped on Saturday for Monday's date every week which caused much of the meat and veggies to be in the containers 2-3 days longer than the allotted amount of time. Mark and the schedule was an absolute disaster me and at least 2 other employees complained to the labor board about him. One employee asked for more hours and they got more days, but LESS hours than they normally get. Mark treats his employees as subhuman giving them part time hours at minimum wages (not even worth taking the job if offered it). Mark was always saying they're not making enough money to keep them open in Saturdays.... So frankly, I hope they close!  Frankly, I don't recommend this Subway at all I hope they go out of business.

Alot of 5 stars so I guess I came in on the wrong day at the wrong time. 20 minutes before closing, the employee had already broken down the serving area. I ordered a meatball sub. Usually the meatballs are kept warm when in the pan and dropped in the warmer. Since she had pulled everything, the meatballs were cold. She grabs some wax paper and picks the meatballs up with her hand, using the wax paper instead of a utensil. That's because she had taken all the utensils to the back as though she would not be serving anymore customers the last 20 minutes.  Anyways, she then places the meatballs in the microwave. She asked me what kind of bread and I told her. She asked me what what kind of bread again and I told her again. Yep, she asked me again and I told her for the third time. She seem so preoccupied with leaving rather than serve me attentively. This Subway closes at 7:00pm so I would not go there after 6:30pm if you want the service these 5-stars folks got.
